---
title: Brown Sugar & Bacon Stuffed French Toast with Cinnamon Maple Syrup & Fruit Salad
description: This French toast has super-cozy vibes: crunchy almonds, warming cinnamon, and rich maple syrup, but with a HF twist! Sourdough slices are spread with whipped brown sugar cream cheese, sandwiched with crispy bacon, dipped in a sweet, creamy egg mixture, pan-fried in butter, then baked until golden and custardy. Before serving, you’ll drizzle the plates generously with cinnamon-infused maple syrup, sprinkle with almonds, and serve it all with a fresh fruit salad. It’s a maple-solutely perfect brunch idea for the family (or a special brekkie just for two).
